T:Magus_CF_MediumArmorProficiency|true	FACT:Magus_CF_HeavyArmorProficiency|true	FACT:Magus_Archetype_SpellRecall|true	FACT:Magus_Archetype_MediumArmorProficiency|true	FACT:Magus_Archetype_HeavyArmorProficiency|true

# Stygian Striker
Class Skills										KEY:Stygian Striker ~ Class Skills				CATEGORY:Special Ability			TYPE:Magus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																																																																																																																																																DESC:[not implemented]A stygian striker gains Stealth as a class skill and loses Knowledge (dungeoneering).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Saving Throws										KEY:Stygian Striker ~ Saving Throws				CATEGORY:Special Ability			TYPE:Magus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																																																																																																																																																DESC:[not implemented]Rather than its normal saving throws, a stygian striker has the same saving throws as a bard (good Reflex and Will saves, poor Fortitude save).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Arcane Shadows										KEY:Stygian Striker ~ Arcane Shadows			CATEGORY:Special Ability			TYPE:Magus Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																																																																																																																																														DESC:[not implemented]At 4th level, the stygian striker can expend a point from his arcane pool as a swift action to vanish for 1 round per stygian striker level obtained, as invisibility. This ability replaces spell recall. The magus gains spell recall when he would normally gain improved spell recall.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Evasion											KEY:Stygian Striker ~ Evasion					CATEGORY:Special Ability			TYPE:Magus Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																																																																														DESC:[not implemented]At 7th level, the stygian striker gains evasion, as the rogue class feature. This ability replaces medium armor.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Hide in Plain Sight									KEY:Stygian Striker ~ Hide in Plain Sight			CATEGORY:Special Ability			TYPE:Magus Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																																																																																																																																														DESC:[not implemented]Starting at 10th level, a stygian striker can use the Stealth skill even while being observed. As long as he is within 10 feet of an area of dim light, a stygian striker can hide himself from view in the open without anything to actually hide behind. He cannot, however, hide in his own shadow. This ability replaces fighter training.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.28
Improved Evasion										KEY:Stygian Striker ~ Improved Evasion			CATEGORY:Special Ability			TYPE:Magus Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																																																																														DESC:[not implemented]At 13th level, the stygian striker gains improved evasion, as the rogue class feature. This ability replaces heavy armor.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.
# Magus Arcana
Nightblade Art										KEY:Stygian Arcana ~ Nightblade Art				CATEGORY:Special Ability			TYPE:MagusArcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural								PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Magus Archetype ~ Stygian Striker																																																																																																																													DESC:[not implemented]The stygian striker gains a nightblade art, using his magus level in place of his nightblade level and his Intelligence modifier in place of his Charisma modifier. He may only choose nightblade arts that require spending a shadow surge to use, such as dusk strike or shadow motion. In place of shadow surges, he may spend points from his arcane pool as if they were shadow surges. The stygian striker can take this arcana multiple times; each time he takes it, he must select a different nightblade art.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.28

